			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Ramius Corporation - headquartered in Ottawa, Canada - develops and delivers social software that improves marketing research, enterprise innovation, group communication and streamlines business processes. Through our software platforms and managed community services, we provide easy-to-use tools that enable clients to build strong business relationships with customers, employees and other target audiences.</p>
<p>
	Ramius&#39; latest platform, Sixent Enterprise, is a feature-rich, robust and scalable social networking and group collaboration suite built entirely in Java.</p>
<p>
	As a technology innovator, we continuously seek talented, highly motivated individuals to contribute to our success. All employees are true partners in the company&#39;s growth and are given equal opportunity to understand the business and affect the decisions that drive our success.</p>
<p>
	Leading Ramius customers include: NASA, IEEE, SAP, American Marketing Association, Nortel, Scottsdale Institute, Dreamworks and the World Bank.</p>
<p>
	Ramius currently has an opening for a full-time Implementation Engineer with HTML, CSS and JavaScript experience to work out of its Ottawa, Canada office.</p>
<p>
	Ramius is searching for a talented Implementation Engineer to join us as we create a new future in social networking and Web-based collaboration. As a part of our growing and dynamic Professional Services team, you will configure, customize, implement and maintain our Sixent Enterprise and CommunityZero products for enterprise customers using a combination of CSS, JavaScript and HTML skills.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Participate in and lead customer co-design and configuration sessions</li>
	<li>
		Design and build interface changes and produce standards-compliant JavaScript, XHTML and CSS that is cross-browser compatible and adheres to the provided specifications</li>
	<li>
		Deliver support to customers throughout the implementation and afterwards during the launch transition</li>
	<li>
		Deliver custom Sixent Enterprise and CommunityZero training to enterprise clients</li>
	<li>
		Review and feedback on the technical feasibility of new business proposals</li>
	<li>
		Aid in the testing of new platform features, particularly with respect to introducing them into existing customer sites</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Required Skills and Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Degree or diploma in a computer-related field</li>
	<li>
		Expert knowledge of JavaScript, XHTML and CSS</li>
	<li>
		Customer support and resolution of issues</li>
	<li>
		Solid understanding of Web development tools and technologies</li>
	<li>
		Skilled at analyzing and solving browser compatibility challenges</li>
	<li>
		Ability to maintain consistent and well-commented JavaScript, HTML and CSS markup</li>
	<li>
		Demonstrated ability to use Adobe Photoshop or an equivalent graphics package</li>
	<li>
		Ability to multi-task in a fast paced environment</li>
	<li>
		Ability to develop and adhere to requirements</li>
	<li>
		Strong attention to detail</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Applicants with strong experience in any of the following are preferred:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Java programming</li>
	<li>
		XML, SQL and PHP</li>
	<li>
		Developing interfaces for Web applications</li>
	<li>
		Adobe Flash / Flex</li>
	<li>
		Microsoft Excel</li>
</ul>
<p>
	Qualified applicants are invited to submit a resume with a cover letter, quoting salary expectations, outlining how your skills and experience meet the above requirements.</p>
<p>
	Where possible, we recommend you submit representative samples of your work to support your application.</p>
